Lesson 1 - Decision Trees

ID3 Algorithm

Loop:
  - A <- Best Attribute
  - Assign A as decision attribute for Node
  - For each Value of A
    - Create descendent of Node
  - Sort Training Examples to leaves
  - If examples Perfectly Classified
    - STOP
    
    
Best attribute -> Maximazie-> Gain(S,A) = Entropy(S) - sum(|Sv|*Entropy(Sv)/|S|) on v
                  S - Training Examples, A - attribute
               
               
    
    
  
